    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The horizontal timbers laid across the principal rafters and supporting the common rafters in a roof. Purlins differ from beams in roof construction in that purlins usually do not support any other members, instead supporting loads from the roof deck.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
